{"questionId":"2967000","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>∈</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>, let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo></math> denote the maximum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>S</mi><mo>)</mo></math> across all possible values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> at which it occurs.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>considering <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>M</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo></math> for higher values of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>81</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A0A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>12</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>82</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>41</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2967000","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.2f","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-an